---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"audit\", \"--help\"])"
---
Audit the current repo (or the whole org) against lab standards

Usage: hpds audit [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  all            Audit every repo in the GitHub org
  report-github  Post audit results to GitHub (sticky PR comment, dedup'd issues)
  help           Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -v, --verbose          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)
  -q, --quiet            Suppress all output except errors
      --format <FORMAT>  Output format [default: text] [possible values: text, json]
      --no-color         Disable colored output
      --config <PATH>    Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml
      --strict           Exit 1 on warnings too (they stay warnings in the report)
  -h, --help             Print help
